**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** [Insert Vehicle Information]
**Date of Inspection:** [Insert Date]

**Location of Damage:**
- The front fender near the wheel well appears to have sustained damage.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage seems to be a dent or indentation in the fender. There is visible distortion in the metal, indicating that the paint has been disturbed, likely due to a collision or impact.
- The area around the dent shows signs of paint chipping and possibly some minor scratches, suggesting that the impact was not severe but enough to cause noticeable damage.

**Additional Notes:**
- The surrounding area of the fender appears to be intact with no other visible damage.
- The tire and wheel well do not show any signs of damage.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained damage to the front fender near the wheel well. The damage is localized and does not appear to extend to other parts of the vehicle. Further inspection may be necessary to determine the extent of the damage and the appropriate course of action.
